---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
    title="Claude Code Workshop | tcplot(Data Visualization Twin Cities)"
    description="AI-assisted coding workshop for data visualization practitioners using Claude Code."
>
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-8 mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                Upcoming: Claude Code for Data Visualization — May 23rd
            </h2>

            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                AI-assisted coding is changing how visualization practitioners
                prototype, iterate, and ship. In this hands-on workshop, we'll
                get you up and running with Claude Code — Anthropic's agentic
                coding tool — and put it to work on real dataviz problems. No
                prior experience with AI coding tools required.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Whether you're deep in D3, grinding through ggplot2, or
                somewhere in between, you'll leave with a working setup and a
                concrete sense of where Claude Code fits (and doesn't fit) in a
                practitioner's workflow.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                Location & Logistics
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <span
                        ><strong class="text-gray-900">When:</strong> Saturday, May
                        23 · 10:00 AM to 12:00 PM CDT</span
                    >
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <span
                        ><strong class="text-gray-900">Where:</strong> The Coffee
                        Shop NE, 2852 Johnson St NE, Minneapolis, MN</span
                    >
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <span>Make sure to bring your laptop and charger.</span>
                </li>
            </ul>

            <div class="flex justify-center mt-12">
                <div class="max-w-2xl w-full rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                    <img
                        src="/images/claudecode1.png"
                        alt="Claude Code terminal running in front of a Stanford Torus space habitat with lush gardens"
                        class="w-full h-auto object-contain"
                    />
                </div>
            </div>

            <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-gray-300 pl-6 mt-12 mb-12">
                <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed italic">
                    "I don't know what the AI-enabled future looks like, but the last time I felt this excited by the potential for creating (almost) anything I could imagine was when I learned HTML as a teenager in the mid-90s.
                </p>
                <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed italic mt-4">
                    The ability to bring a visualization, dashboard, or analytic pipeline to life nearly instantaneously is a game-changer for conveying knowledge and insights. We still need humans to conceptualize these visualizations, dashboards, and pipelines so that they are meaningful and useful to others, but the technical barriers that have prevented us from telling maximally compelling stories with data have been massively reduced."
                </p>
                <p class="text-base text-gray-500 mt-3">
                    —Julian Wolfson on LinkedIn
                </p>
            </blockquote>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-3">
                Workshop Prompts
            </h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                We'll build a D3 multi-line chart of Metro Transit ridership from scratch, prompt by prompt:
            </p>
            <ol class="space-y-4 text-gray-600 mb-12">
                <li class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Prompt 1 — Get something on screen</li>
                <li class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Prompt 2 — Fix the first thing that's wrong</li>
                <li class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Prompt 3 — Add the pandemic context</li>
                <li class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Prompt 4 — Make it interactive</li>
                <li class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Prompt 5 — A judgment call Claude can't make for you</li>
                <li class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Prompt 6 — Ship it</li>
            </ol>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-3">
                Dataset
            </h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                Federal Transit Administration. "Monthly Module Adjusted Data Release." <em>National Transit Database</em>, U.S. Department of Transportation, May 2026, <a
                    href="https://www.transit.dot.gov/ntd/data-product/monthly-module-adjusted-data-release"
                    target="_blank"
                    rel="noopener noreferrer"
                    class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                    >www.transit.dot.gov/ntd/data-product/monthly-module-adjusted-data-release</a>.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                Download Data
            </h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                Metro Transit ridership CSVs, ready to use:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 mb-6">
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <a href="/data/Master-Table 1.csv" download class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Master Table</a>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <a href="/data/UPT-Table 1.csv" download class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">UPT (Unlinked Passenger Trips)</a>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <a href="/data/UPT Estimates-Table 1.csv" download class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">UPT Estimates</a>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <a href="/data/Calendar Year UPT-Table 1.csv" download class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Calendar Year UPT</a>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <a href="/data/VRM-Table 1.csv" download class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">VRM (Vehicle Revenue Miles)</a>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <a href="/data/VRM Estimates-Table 1.csv" download class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">VRM Estimates</a>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <a href="/data/Calendar Year VRM-Table 1.csv" download class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Calendar Year VRM</a>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <a href="/data/VRH-Table 1.csv" download class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">VRH (Vehicle Revenue Hours)</a>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <a href="/data/VOMS-Table 1.csv" download class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">VOMS (Vehicles Operated in Max Service)</a>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <a href="/data/Read Me-Table 1.csv" download class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Read Me</a>
                </li>
            </ul>

            <div class="flex justify-center mt-12">
                <div class="max-w-2xl w-full rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                    <img
                        src="/images/claudecode2.png"
                        alt="Claude Code terminal running in front of the Tereshkova space station"
                        class="w-full h-auto object-contain"
                    />
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>
